WorkItem.Description:
I've been trying everything I know to get PHPExcel to read this file, but nothing works. identify() can't event tell me what it is. But it's not a CSV or XML file and opens perfectly in my version Excel on my Mac.

Any help would be appreciated.

Philip

Comments.Message: Excel 2013 opens it in protected mode, which I currently have set for files written using Excel4 (1992) or below. Further checks show that it is actually BIFF4. That means it was created/saved as an OLE1 document (a different format to the later BIFF5-8 OLE2 formats) that only supported a single worksheet. Unfortunately, PHPExcel doesn't support reading any BIFF versions below BIFF5.
